                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Jan. 8: The Orissa government has promised to remove the hurdles in the proposed Rs 1 lakh crore investment by Posco and ArcelorMittal. There will be opposition for political purposes. In a democracy it happens. But Orissa is making all efforts to give land. Be it Posco or ArcelorMittal, discussions are on, P. C. Ghadai, state finance minister, said.                            
	 Mumbai/New Delhi, Jan. 8: The Air India board today began deliberations on crucial financial issues such as bridge loans for aircraft deliveries, its plans for commercial transformation and reinventing the AI brand.                            
	 Mumbai Jan. 8: Market regulator Sebi today streamlined trading in equity-linked derivatives across bourses by fixing lot sizes according to the price of these securities.                            
	 New York, Jan. 8: Indian-American Anil Kumar  former director of consulting firm McKinsey  has pleaded guilty to fraud charges in one of the largest insider trading cases in the US.                                                                                                                          
